            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-236-person1944">
                  ELEANOR 
                  REDDING
               <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1944" type="surname" value="REDDING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1944" type="given" value="ELEANOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1944" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . 
               <persName id="t18300916-236-person1945">
                  Jeremiah 
                  Redding
               <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1945" type="surname" value="Redding"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1945" type="given" value="Jeremiah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1945" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             is my son - these articles were his property. On the 11th of July the prisoner took them out of my room about four o'clock in the morning - I was in bed; he opened the door, came in, and took them - my son was in the next bed, and I called to him.</p>
               <p>JEREMIAH REDDING. My mother told me some person had taken my things; I ran into the passage, the prisoner dropped my boots, and went out at the door - I ran to the window, and called Stop thief! he got out of my sight, but I know he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-236-person1946">
                  MAURICE 
                  NICHOLASS
               <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1946" type="surname" value="NICHOLASS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1946" type="given" value="MAURICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1946" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the cry of Stop thief! and saw the prisoner run - I went and took him, and found the braces and trousers in his hat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that the prosecutor had been tried himself, and that he had struck him.</p>
               <p>JEREMIAH REDDING. I did not; he took my things off a line - I was tried here twelve months ago.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-236-person1947">
                  MAURICE 
                  NICHOLASS
               <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1947" type="surname" value="NICHOLASS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1947" type="given" value="MAURICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-236-person1947" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner back - Mrs. Redding said he had taken the things; he said, "I have done it, and I dare say I shall be transported;" the house is No. 21, in the Coal-yard.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 24.</p>
